name: Spectacled Owl
description:
Common Name: Spectacled Owl
Latin Name: Pulsatrix perspicillata
Location: tropical forests of Central and South America
Conservation Status: Least Concern

The largest of the tropical owl species, the spectacled owl gets it’s name from the white feather “spectacles” around their eyes.

Photographed at Minnesota Zoo
Nikon D5300
June 25, 2014
